<h1>PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
<h4><i>Last modified on August 9, 2022</i></h4>

By accessing or using our products and services ("Services" or “MTM App”), which are provided by Pironi Ltd (“MTM”), you agree to this Privacy Policy and to our Terms of Service (the “Terms”). Please read them carefully. These Terms are effective beginning when you first download, install, access, or use the Services. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THESE TERMS, PLEASE DO NOT USE THE SERVICES. If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us. 
<br></br>
INFORMATION MTM COLLECTS<br></br>
When you register for MTM, you voluntarily give us information such as your name and email address. We also collect user data related to the use of the app, such as the goals that each user sets, the tasks that each user adds, and so on. We also collect information about the browsers and devices you use to access MTM. We may also collect aggregated, anonymous user data about the use of the app, such as location information. We only collect personal data required to deliver our services, and we only store it to the extent that it is essential to perform these services.
<br></br>
As an MTM user, you voluntarily add information about your Goals, Tasks, and everything else that you enter in the app. You represent and warrant that you have permission from your business partners, employers, employees, work colleagues, and from other third parties to enter this information in the MTM app. You will hold harmless and indemnify MTM and its affiliates, officers, agents, and employees from any claim, suit or action arising from or related to the use of the Services or violation of these terms, including any liability or expense arising from claims, losses, direct or indirect damages, suits, judgments, litigation costs and attorneys' fees. You will also hold MTM harmless for any damage occurring, whether directly or indirectly, from events such as the deletion of this information or the appropriation of this information by MTM or by third parties not authorised by MTM.
<br></br>
MTM uses third party services and hosting partners who are GDPR-compliant. MTM will never sell your personal data to a third party. ​We will protect personal information by reasonable security safeguards against loss or theft, as well as unauthorised access, disclosure, copying, use or modification. You have the right to: (1) request to see any information we hold about you and correct it if it’s wrong, (2) request your data is deleted, (3) request your data is not used for certain purposes.
<br></br>
<br></br>
WHY MTM COLLECTS DATA<br></br>
We use data to build better services. Your information will only be used internally for the purposes described below:
To deliver our services or information you requested, and to process and complete any transactions.
To provide you with recommendations on how to improve the usage of our services and on how to improve your own time management
To ensure our services are working as intended, such as tracking outages or troubleshooting issues that you report to us.
To make improvements to our services - for example, to analyse usage and trends with anonymous user data, and to improve the quality of our service and user experience.
To interact with you directly (through email addresses you provide us by communicating with us via email or through voluntary activities such as site registration or survey participation). 
To help improve the safety and reliability of our services.
<br></br>
We use different technologies to process your information for these purposes. You're welcome to contact us to ask for our confirmation whenever you feel concerned about how your personal information is being processed, where and for what purpose.
<br></br>
<br></br>
HOW CAN I DELETE MY ACCOUNT?<br></br>
You can delete your MTM account by contacting us. If you delete your Account, any association between your Account and information we store will no longer be accessible through your Account. We will stop providing products and/or services to you and delete your personal information as required by you.
<br></br>
<br></br>
CHANGES TO THIS POLICY<br></br>
We may change our Privacy Policy from time to time. This page always indicates the date the latest changes were published. Please check back periodically to keep informed of updates or changes to this Privacy Policy. By continuing to access and to use MTM, you are agreeing to be bound by the revised policy.
